.TH SINGINE-LOGSEQ 1 "2026-03-17" "singine 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
singine-logseq \- inspect Logseq graphs and export them to Org and XML
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B singine logseq inspect
[\fB--base-url\fR \fIURL\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine logseq ping
[\fB--base-url\fR \fIURL\fR] [\fB--token\fR \fITOKEN\fR] [\fB--timeout\fR \fISECONDS\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine logseq graphs
[\fB--root\fR \fIDIR\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine logseq export-org
\fB--graph\fR \fINAME-OR-PATH\fR
[\fB--root\fR \fIDIR\fR] [\fB--output\fR \fIFILE\fR]
[\fB--limit\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB--pages-only\fR | \fB--journals-only\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.PP
.B singine logseq export-xml
\fB--graph\fR \fINAME-OR-PATH\fR
\fB--org-output\fR \fIORGFILE\fR
\fB--xml-output\fR \fIXMLFILE\fR
[\fB--root\fR \fIDIR\fR]
[\fB--om-to-xml-repo\fR \fIDIR\fR]
[\fB--elisp-load-path\fR \fIDIR\fR]
[\fB--emacs-bin\fR \fIPROGRAM\fR]
[\fB--limit\fR \fIN\fR] [\fB--pages-only\fR | \fB--journals-only\fR] [\fB--json\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B logseq
command family reports the Logseq HTTP API defaults that Singine uses when it
prefers API ingestion over filesystem fallback, and it can also discover local
Logseq graph roots and render their Markdown content into Org mode and XML.
.PP
Singine's current default is:
.IP
\fBhttp://127.0.0.1:12315/api\fR
.PP
with the bearer token sourced from
.BR LOGSEQ_API_TOKEN .
When the API is unavailable, Singine falls back to local graph directories
under \fI~/ws/logseq\fR.
.PP
For the XML export path, Singine expects a local checkout of Norman Walsh's
\fBorg-to-xml\fR project and Emacs-loadable dependencies such as
\fBorg-ml\fR, \fBdash.el\fR, and \fBs.el\fR. The default workspace layout used
by the command examples is:
.IP \(bu 2
\fI/Users/skh/ws/git/codeberg/ndw/org-to-xml\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI/Users/skh/ws/git/github/ndwarshuis/org-ml\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI/Users/skh/ws/git/github/magnars/dash.el\fR
.IP \(bu 2
\fI/Users/skh/ws/git/github/magnars/s.el\fR
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B inspect
Print the effective base URL, API endpoint, token presence flag, filesystem
fallback hint, and publication alignment with the activity taxonomy and the
SilkPage docs tree.
.TP
.B ping
POST \fBlogseq.App.getCurrentGraph\fR to the configured Logseq API endpoint.
.TP
.B graphs
Discover local Logseq graph base directories. Singine checks direct graph roots
with \fIpages/\fR and \fIjournals/\fR, and versioned graphs under
\fIversion-files/base\fR. Default search roots are \fI~/ws/logseq\fR and the
versioned website graph under \fI~/ws/git/github/sindoc/website/logseq\fR.
.TP
.B export-org
Resolve a graph by name or path and render it as a consolidated Org document.
This is intended as the hand-off point to Emacs and Org mode tooling.
.TP
.B export-xml
Generate an Org document and then invoke Emacs in batch mode to call Norman
Walsh's \fBom-to-xml.el\fR from the \fBorg-to-xml\fR project. Singine also
adds extra Emacs load paths for dependencies such as \fBorg-ml\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
singine logseq inspect
singine logseq inspect --json
singine logseq ping --token "$LOGSEQ_API_TOKEN" --json
singine logseq graphs --json
singine logseq export-org --graph kernel --output /tmp/kernel.org
singine logseq export-org \\
  --graph /Users/skh/ws/git/github/sindoc/website/logseq \\
  --limit 5
singine logseq export-xml \\
  --graph kernel \\
  --org-output /tmp/kernel.org \\
  --xml-output /tmp/kernel.xml \\
  --om-to-xml-repo /Users/skh/ws/git/codeberg/ndw/org-to-xml \\
  --elisp-load-path /Users/skh/ws/git/github/ndwarshuis/org-ml \\
  --json
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR singine (1),
.BR singine-server (1),
.BR singine-snapshot (1),
.BR singine-man (1)
